Ad Group ID.description: The identifier of the ad group.

Product Ad ID.description: The identifier of the Product ad.

Month.description: Month will be represented as the first day of the month in YYYY-MM-DD format. Either Day, Week or Month must be queried.

Week.description: Week will be represented as the first day of the week in YYYY-MM-DD format. This will always be Monday. Either Day, Week or Month must be queried.

Day.description: The date. Either Day, Week or Month must be queried.

Device Type.description: Device type of the user: Desktop, Tablet, Phone, Unknown. Note that Device Type data is only available after the field is launched. If you run it for a previous date, it will return NONE in the Device Type column.

Post Click Conversions.description: The total number of post click conversions.

Post Impression Conversions.description: The total number of post view conversions.

Conversions.description: The total number of conversions, includes both post click and post view conversions. For app install campaigns the default conversion windows are 7 days post-click and 1 day post view. For website conversions the default windows are 30 days post-click and 2 days post-view.

Total Conversions.description: A synonym for the Conversions field (is kept for backwards compatibility).

Spend.description: The unadjusted spend amount. Please note that adjustments - meaning any corrections due to issues like overcharging - can be queried using the adjustment_stats cube.

Ad Extn Impressions.description: Total impressions for which an ad extension was displayed.

Ad Extn Clicks.description: Total clicks on an ad extension link (rather than on the ad landing URL).

Ad Extn Conversions.description: Total conversions which were attributed back to an ad extension link click.

Ad Extn Spend.description: The spend resulting from clicking on an ad extension link.

Video 25% Complete.description: Number of times the video played to 25% of its length.

Video 50% Complete.description: Number of times the video played to 50% of its length.

Video 75% Complete.description: Number of times the video played to 75% of its length.

Video 100% Complete.description: Number of times the video played to 100% of its length.

Video Closed.description: The number of times the video was closed.

Video Skipped.description: The number of times the video was skipped.

Video after 30 seconds view.description: The number of times the video played longer than 30 seconds.

In App Post Click Convs.description: Total Post Click Conversions that occurred in the app after it was installed. These conversions occurred in the app, but were attributed to clicks made on an ad outside of the app.

In App Post View Convs.description: Total Post View Conversions that occurred in the app after it was installed. These conversions occurred in the app, but were attributed to impressions made on an ad outside of the app.

In App Post Install Convs.description: Total Post Install Conversions that occurred in the app after it was installed. These conversions occurred in the app, but were attributed to the installation made on an ad outside of the app.

Opens.description: Number of impressions of the Mail Ad asset.

Saves.description: Number of users who clicked save.

Forwards.description: Number of email addresses the email was forwarded to.

Click Outs.description: Number of users to clicked out to advertiser landing page.

Fact Conversion Counting.description: The way your conversions were counted for the campaign during the report time range (ALL_PER_INTERACTION, ONE_PER_INTERACTION).
